Inventory file:
---------------

*)Inventory is a file in Ansible that contains the list of target servers (hosts) and host groups managed by Ansible.
  It tells Ansible which servers to connect to and manage.

Ex: inside inventory.ini ( file name ), it should be like below so then control-node will call the group names either 'prod or test' based on the requirement
    then perform the tasks accordingly after you run the playbook.

[prod]
12.13.14.15
12.13.14.15

[test]
12.13.14.15


Here, [prod] and [test] are the group names

