- name: Ping the server
  hosts: 12.13.14.15
  tasks:
  - name: ping
    ansible.builtin.ping:
	
	
	
	
Example-2: How to install a package or software, start the service and auto restart the service on reboot?

- name: Intall the Nginx
  hosts: frontend
  become: yes
  
  tasks:
  - name: Nginx install
    ansible.builtin.package:
	  name: Nginx
	  state: present
	  
  - name: start nginx
    ansible.builtin.service:
	  name: start
	  state: started
	  enabled: yes
  
  
#)NOTE:
--------
  
*)hosts: frontend(group name) --> decides the target server
*)become: yes --> it will run the tasks with sudo permissions(root user) in the managed(remote) server.
*)enabled: yes --> service will be auto-restart on the reboot 
 
